Banco Financiero & de Ahorros
SA, the parent company of Spanish lender  Bankia (BKIA) , had a net
loss of 278.3 million euros ($368.3 million) in the second
half of 2011, it said today in a filing.  The company had net income of 40.9 million euros for
the full year. The bank was created last year when Bankia
was formed by the merger of seven savings banks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
